1
00:00:03,671 --> 00:00:05,571
     Twilight: THIS happened
       while we were gone?

2
00:00:06,273 --> 00:00:08,307
Applejack: Wow! Those are
all the places we went

3
00:00:08,409 --> 00:00:10,042
when we left to
save Equestria!

4
00:00:10,144 --> 00:00:13,545
  Ugh! There's that HORRID town
   where we were almost sold!

5
00:00:13,747 --> 00:00:16,248
          The pirates! They were
             pretty awesome...

6
00:00:16,450 --> 00:00:18,851
     er.. once they decided not
     to throw us overboard.

7
00:00:19,053 --> 00:00:21,286
  And Mt. Aris! Ooo, Starlight!

8
00:00:21,688 --> 00:00:28,193
  Did you know we made seashell
necklaces for AAALLL-LLLL the seaponies?

9
00:00:28,595 --> 00:00:29,495
     I...

10
00:00:29,797 --> 00:00:30,629
     you...

11
00:00:30,731 --> 00:00:31,447
   Really?

12
00:00:31,948 --> 00:00:33,464
What about that unicorn?

13
00:00:33,567 --> 00:00:35,167
The one who attacked
   Canterlot?

14
00:00:35,469 --> 00:00:37,836
Tempest. I invited her
to come to Ponyville,

15
00:00:37,938 --> 00:00:39,304
but she wanted to
spread the word

16
00:00:39,406 --> 00:00:40,806
of the Storm
King's defeat...

17
00:00:40,908 --> 00:00:42,741
and share what she
learned about friendship.

18
00:00:42,843 --> 00:00:45,210
       Y'all think that's
        why the map grew?

19
00:00:45,312 --> 00:00:47,646
        Friendship quests
        beyond Equestria?

20
00:00:47,848 --> 00:00:49,065
                    I hope not.

21
00:00:49,166 --> 00:00:51,583
      I've had quite enough
    life-threatening adventures,

22
00:00:51,685 --> 00:00:52,918
            thank you very much.

23
00:00:55,189 --> 00:00:57,890
How many friendship quests do
you think we need to go on

24
00:00:58,192 --> 00:01:00,793
before we have to
expand the throne room?

25
00:01:01,395 --> 00:01:02,962
    We can't do it all alone.

26
00:01:03,364 --> 00:01:04,581
          Sure we can!

27
00:01:04,682 --> 00:01:07,199
 We just need to knock this wall
     down, get some paint--

28
00:01:07,301 --> 00:01:09,801
     No. I mean the world is
  filled with so many different

29
00:01:09,903 --> 00:01:11,871
   creatures who know nothing
        about friendship.

30
00:01:12,073 --> 00:01:14,439
 We need help if we're gonna
teach them all about friendship.

31
00:01:14,641 --> 00:01:15,591
          Lots of help.

32
00:01:15,892 --> 00:01:17,442
      Rarity: Perhaps. But
        where does one go

33
00:01:17,545 --> 00:01:19,345
         to learn about
          friendship?

34
00:01:19,947 --> 00:01:22,281
   Here! They can all go here!

35
00:01:22,483 --> 00:01:24,616
       Because we're gonna
         open a school!

36
00:02:03,957 --> 00:02:05,891
       Celestia: I think a
      School of Friendship

37
00:02:05,993 --> 00:02:08,026
         is a wonderful
         idea, Twilight.

38
00:02:08,128 --> 00:02:10,028
                   I'll help in
                  any way I can.

39
00:02:13,834 --> 00:02:15,267
  I just have a few questions:

40
00:02:15,369 --> 00:02:16,802
       What time should
     school start each day?

41
00:02:16,903 --> 00:02:18,536
It really de-
               What's the ideal
               length for class?

42
00:02:18,639 --> 00:02:19,722
          Do you test regularly?

43
00:02:19,823 --> 00:02:21,506
Oh, well that's--
                   What about
                 class projects?

44
00:02:21,607 --> 00:02:23,190
   That's a ver--
               Assigned seating?
                 Open seating?

45
00:02:23,291 --> 00:02:25,074
                  Or is that too
                   unstructured?

46
00:02:25,579 --> 00:02:28,547
Oh, Twilight! You
were my star pupil.

47
00:02:28,749 --> 00:02:31,417
If anyone knows how to
run a school, it's you.

48
00:02:32,119 --> 00:02:34,453
    There's a big difference
   between attending a school

49
00:02:34,555 --> 00:02:35,371
        and running one.

50
00:02:35,472 --> 00:02:37,288
     It's not like there's a
       rulebook to follow.

51
00:02:37,591 --> 00:02:39,057
Actually, there is.

52
00:02:39,159 --> 00:02:41,560
The EEA guidebook
is very specific

53
00:02:41,662 --> 00:02:42,894
about how to
run a school.

54
00:02:42,996 --> 00:02:45,697
             The EEA? I've never
               heard of that.

55
00:02:46,099 --> 00:02:47,199
                   Should I have
                  heard of that!?

56
00:02:47,601 --> 00:02:50,335
Of course not, you've never
run a school before!

57
00:02:50,437 --> 00:02:52,804
The Equestria Education
Association is a board

58
00:02:52,906 --> 00:02:56,141
of learned ponies that oversee
every school in Equestria.

59
00:02:56,343 --> 00:02:57,576
               Even YOUR school?

60
00:02:57,978 --> 00:02:59,511
But you're...YOU!

61
00:03:00,013 --> 00:03:02,114
Not even a Princess can
do whatever she likes

62
00:03:02,216 --> 00:03:04,683
when it comes to shaping
young pony minds.

63
00:03:04,885 --> 00:03:08,053
The EEA ensures that whether
it's unicorns studying magic,

64
00:03:08,355 --> 00:03:09,555
pegasi learning weather,

65
00:03:09,657 --> 00:03:11,890
or earth ponies
researching agriculture,

66
00:03:12,092 --> 00:03:15,194
all schools are held to
the same high standard.

67
00:03:15,596 --> 00:03:16,928
They'll need to
approve your plan

68
00:03:17,030 --> 00:03:18,797
before you can
move forward.

69
00:03:19,599 --> 00:03:20,565
                      OK, Spike.

70
00:03:20,667 --> 00:03:22,701
           Looks like we have a
           presentation to make!

71
00:03:22,903 --> 00:03:26,439
Pff. After everything we've been
through, how hard can that be?

72
00:03:29,643 --> 00:03:31,510
    I'm gonna go with
      really hard.

73
00:03:31,912 --> 00:03:34,246
Uh. Hello. My name is--

74
00:03:34,348 --> 00:03:37,048
               Princess Twilight
                 Sparkle.

75
00:03:37,150 --> 00:03:39,117
     I am Chancellor Neighsay.

76
00:03:39,219 --> 00:03:41,353
       Equestria owes you
          a great debt.

77
00:03:41,655 --> 00:03:45,390
 But Princess or no, we expect
    you to do things by...

78
00:03:45,892 --> 00:03:46,458
            The...

79
00:03:46,560 --> 00:03:47,193
           Book!

80
00:03:51,098 --> 00:03:52,698
I think you'll
find my curriculum

81
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:54,899
meets all your
requirements, Chancellor.

82
00:04:00,841 --> 00:04:03,742
 And can we trust you to follow
   through with this plan?

83
00:04:03,944 --> 00:04:05,811
      Or will you leave the
        school unattended

84
00:04:05,913 --> 00:04:08,848
      to gallop off on your
     ... adventures?

85
00:04:09,750 --> 00:04:12,384
My journey beyond Equestria
showed me first hoof

86
00:04:12,486 --> 00:04:15,053
that the threats out there
are greater than we imagined.

87
00:04:18,859 --> 00:04:20,692
If we want to keep
our land safe,

88
00:04:20,794 --> 00:04:22,561
and create a
friendlier tomorrow,

89
00:04:22,663 --> 00:04:25,464
we need to teach the magic
of friendship far and wide.

90
00:04:25,966 --> 00:04:29,735
  A school for ponies to learn
  how to protect themselves...

91
00:04:30,637 --> 00:04:33,705
    Uh, more like respecting
  differences and communicating.

92
00:04:37,344 --> 00:04:39,010
        The EEA concurs.

93
00:04:39,112 --> 00:04:42,481
  Everypony should be prepared
   to defend our way of life.

94
00:04:43,083 --> 00:04:45,484
  So, if your work is in order,

95
00:04:45,886 --> 00:04:49,621
      provisional EEA
      approval is granted.

96
00:04:50,323 --> 00:04:52,924
  We will need to observe your
     school up and running

97
00:04:53,026 --> 00:04:55,627
        before it can be
        fully accredited.

98
00:04:55,929 --> 00:04:58,664
Then please, join us for
Friends and Family Day.

99
00:04:58,866 --> 00:05:00,932
It'll be a perfect time
to see our progress!

100
00:05:17,985 --> 00:05:19,050
  Rainbow Dash: It's too much!

101
00:05:19,252 --> 00:05:21,019
            TOO MUCH!

102
00:05:21,121 --> 00:05:22,772
      Rarity: Ah! You think so!?

103
00:05:22,973 --> 00:05:25,824
  I had hoped dressing the part
  would help me<i> feel</i> the part.

104
00:05:26,126 --> 00:05:27,526
                 Not your dress!

105
00:05:27,728 --> 00:05:30,729
       This! Us! Teaching?

106
00:05:30,831 --> 00:05:33,231
       They're gonna think
         I'm an egghead!

107
00:05:35,469 --> 00:05:38,937
  Well, the students are gonna
 LOVE my confetti cannon class.

108
00:05:39,039 --> 00:05:41,006
     It's gonna be.. a blast!

109
00:05:41,976 --> 00:05:44,409
        Um. Hello there.
        I'm your teacher.

110
00:05:44,611 --> 00:05:46,044
     I hope you enjoy class.

111
00:05:46,146 --> 00:05:48,647
   But if you don't enjoy it,
      that's OK, too.

112
00:05:50,784 --> 00:05:52,584
I don't know about all this...

113
00:05:52,786 --> 00:05:54,319
     It's going to be fine.

114
00:05:54,621 --> 00:05:57,356
    Everything about this
    school just feels right.

115
00:05:58,058 --> 00:06:00,358
        See? If Twilight
         isn't stressed,

116
00:06:00,460 --> 00:06:02,394
       you've got nothing
         to worry about!

117
00:06:03,296 --> 00:06:06,398
       And you're SURE you
     want US to be teachers?

118
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:08,300
    In.. classrooms?

119
00:06:08,702 --> 00:06:11,536
The EEA is VERY clear on how
schools should be run.

120
00:06:11,938 --> 00:06:14,139
We have a HUGE
responsibility,

121
00:06:14,241 --> 00:06:16,742
  and I need you all to do
    this by the book.

122
00:06:17,044 --> 00:06:19,278
That means no cannons
in class, Pinkie.

123
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:24,048
               Awwwwww! Not even
                a teeny cannon..?

124
00:06:25,786 --> 00:06:28,752
       I know it's not some big adventure
       against the forces of evil.

125
00:06:28,805 --> 00:06:31,055
      But this could be the
      most important thing

126
00:06:31,158 --> 00:06:32,190
        we've ever done!

127
00:06:32,292 --> 00:06:33,658
      I can't run a school
        of Friendship

128
00:06:33,760 --> 00:06:35,126
    without my best friends.

129
00:06:35,428 --> 00:06:36,628
       Can I count on you?

130
00:06:37,130 --> 00:06:39,264
                Of course you
                can, darling.

131
00:06:39,666 --> 00:06:42,934
Call me Professor
Egghead. I'm in.

132
00:06:45,557 --> 00:06:49,508
   AHHHH! FIRST DAY OF SCHOOL!
       SO MANY NEW PONIES!

133
00:06:49,810 --> 00:06:52,344
About that. ONE thing
I forgot to mention.

134
00:06:52,546 --> 00:06:54,279
     It's not JUST ponies...

135
00:06:59,286 --> 00:07:00,785
            That was unexpected!

136
00:07:06,660 --> 00:07:09,728
   Oooh! Students certainly
   traveled from far and wide

137
00:07:09,830 --> 00:07:11,396
      to attend our school!

138
00:07:11,498 --> 00:07:13,999
Princess Celestia helped me
reach out to all the kingdoms.

139
00:07:14,101 --> 00:07:15,734
After all, friendship
is something

140
00:07:15,836 --> 00:07:18,637
that needs to be shared
with every...creature.

141
00:07:21,274 --> 00:07:22,874
      Welcome to the School
       of Friendship!

142
00:07:23,176 --> 00:07:25,444
       I'm your headmare,
        Twilight Sparkle!

143
00:07:25,646 --> 00:07:27,612
     Please follow Guidance
       Counselor Starlight

144
00:07:27,714 --> 00:07:29,715
     to sign in and get your
       class assignments.

145
00:07:30,017 --> 00:07:31,883
      Then we can show you
      your living quarters!

146
00:07:34,621 --> 00:07:35,987
Whoa, sorry!

147
00:07:36,289 --> 00:07:37,356
I'm Sandbar.

148
00:07:37,658 --> 00:07:39,291
Are you a student
here, too?

149
00:07:39,693 --> 00:07:41,893
          No. I just figured I'd
          randomly stand here

150
00:07:41,995 --> 00:07:43,795
         and see how many ponies
           would walk into me.

151
00:07:44,697 --> 00:07:45,997
    Angry male voice: GALLUS!

152
00:07:48,936 --> 00:07:50,335
                  Grandpa Gruff!

153
00:07:50,437 --> 00:07:51,570
                  What are you
                   doing here?

154
00:07:51,672 --> 00:07:53,438
Flew all the way
from Griffonstone

155
00:07:53,540 --> 00:07:56,140
to introduce Gallus.

156
00:07:57,578 --> 00:07:59,077
            Rainbow Dash, right?

157
00:07:59,179 --> 00:08:00,712
        Gilda told me about you.

158
00:08:00,714 --> 00:08:01,848
               You're a teacher?

159
00:08:01,949 --> 00:08:04,783
              Huh. Thought you'd
                be... cooler.

160
00:08:05,185 --> 00:08:06,486
    Gruff male voice: PONIES!

161
00:08:07,788 --> 00:08:09,922
       Prince Rutherford!

162
00:08:10,524 --> 00:08:11,924
                  This Yona Yak.

163
00:08:12,726 --> 00:08:14,359
        She come to pony school.

164
00:08:14,861 --> 00:08:16,195
                 Make it better.

165
00:08:16,897 --> 00:08:18,897
         Yak can't wait
         to meet ponies

166
00:08:19,199 --> 00:08:21,366
       and tell ALL about
          Yakyakistan!

167
00:08:27,841 --> 00:08:30,476
   Why don't I show you around
  before you destroy the place?

168
00:08:30,978 --> 00:08:32,778
       But dragons are
        better than this.

169
00:08:34,214 --> 00:08:35,347
         Why am I here?

170
00:08:35,449 --> 00:08:39,318
Because as Dragon Lord,
I'm ordering you to be here!

171
00:08:40,220 --> 00:08:43,054
 Hey! Spike! Come meet Smolder.

172
00:08:43,991 --> 00:08:45,190
Great to see you, Ember.

173
00:08:46,927 --> 00:08:49,194
Uh... Which one is Smolder?

174
00:08:53,033 --> 00:08:54,033
                        Ocellus!

175
00:08:54,735 --> 00:08:56,168
                     What did we
                     talk about?

176
00:08:58,705 --> 00:08:59,504
                     I told you.

177
00:08:59,606 --> 00:09:01,206
                    Stay in your
                      own form.

178
00:09:01,308 --> 00:09:02,908
                 It's the polite
                  thing to do.

179
00:09:03,110 --> 00:09:05,210
               Sorry.. She's shy.

180
00:09:06,446 --> 00:09:07,979
What is THAT?

181
00:09:13,186 --> 00:09:14,853
                      No way!

182
00:09:14,955 --> 00:09:17,489
            I didn't know ponies
             could turn into...

183
00:09:17,591 --> 00:09:19,157
              Um...what are you?

184
00:09:19,459 --> 00:09:20,426
A changeling.

185
00:09:20,928 --> 00:09:23,795
      Ponies can turn into
        changelings!?

186
00:09:24,197 --> 00:09:27,366
No. But changelings
can turn into ponies.

187
00:09:27,868 --> 00:09:29,901
     Huh. That's confusing.

188
00:09:33,658 --> 00:09:37,843
  I am General Seaspray of Her
   Majesty Queen Novo's navy.

189
00:09:38,145 --> 00:09:42,080
  I would like to introduce the
  queen's niece, Silverstream.

190
00:09:42,382 --> 00:09:45,884
     This place is amazing!

191
00:09:45,986 --> 00:09:47,953
  I've spent most of my life in
    a coral reef under water.

192
00:09:48,055 --> 00:09:50,055
  I was a seapony. But now I'm
    a hippogriff, long story.

193
00:09:50,157 --> 00:09:53,458
         Anyways... WOW!
         IS THAT A YAK!?

194
00:09:58,432 --> 00:10:00,799
    Thank you so much for
  supporting the grand opening

195
00:10:00,901 --> 00:10:01,951
         of our school.

196
00:10:02,152 --> 00:10:04,802
  I hope you'll all join us for
   Friends and Family Day

197
00:10:04,905 --> 00:10:08,039
   to see the amazing progress
    your students are making!

