00:12:04,291 --> 00:12:05,858
       <i> ♪ Another Class ♪</i>

233
00:12:05,959 --> 00:12:09,026
      <i> ♪ Wish it were more</i>
          <i> of a blast ♪</i>

234
00:12:09,229 --> 00:12:12,230
     <i> ♪ Thought this school</i>
      <i> would be more fun ♪</i>

235
00:12:12,432 --> 00:12:16,167
      <i> ♪ Can't wait for our</i>
      <i> classes to be done ♪</i>

236
00:12:16,269 --> 00:12:19,137
     <i> ♪ Can't mess up</i>
  <i> Can't afford a mistake now ♪</i>

237
00:12:19,439 --> 00:12:21,039
     <i> ♪ No way to have fun ♪</i>

238
00:12:21,141 --> 00:12:22,319
   <i> ♪ Oh, what have I done! ♪</i>

239
00:12:22,420 --> 00:12:25,398
   <i> ♪ Bored with this class ♪</i>
     <i> ♪ Think success. Keep it firmly in sight ♪</i>

240
00:12:25,499 --> 00:12:27,677
      <i> ♪ Wish that we could</i>
        <i> leave en masse ♪</i>

241
00:12:27,981 --> 00:12:29,031
    <i> ♪ We don't have a clue ♪</i>

242
00:12:29,132 --> 00:12:31,582
 <i> ♪ Listen to this one request ♪</i>

243
00:12:31,785 --> 00:12:34,886
       <i> ♪ Make things fun</i>
    <i> we're really stressed ♪</i>

244
00:12:35,388 --> 00:12:40,189
    <i> ♪ Make sure to do things</i>
       <i> by the book nooowwww... ♪</i>

245
00:12:40,794 --> 00:12:44,662
     <i> ♪ Can we tell her this</i>
       <i> thing is a mess? ♪</i>

246
00:12:48,668 --> 00:12:50,068
     Is this what boring is?

247
00:12:50,170 --> 00:12:50,969
           Am I bored?

248
00:12:51,071 --> 00:12:52,571
             Ugh. Please.

249
00:12:52,673 --> 00:12:55,774
      THESE ponies are the
      heroes of Equestria?

250
00:12:55,876 --> 00:12:59,878
  Listen, "these ponies" saved
 all of us from The Storm King.

251
00:13:00,380 --> 00:13:03,081
How? By boring him
into surrender?

252
00:13:03,283 --> 00:13:06,585
    Our teachers are a little
   different than I expected.

253
00:13:06,687 --> 00:13:08,987
        Agh! Pony school
         waste of time!

254
00:13:09,189 --> 00:13:11,356
      YAK school teach how
       to braid Yak hair!

255
00:13:11,458 --> 00:13:13,057
   BRAIDING YAK HAIR IS BEST!

256
00:13:13,159 --> 00:13:14,092
              Whoa!

257
00:13:14,194 --> 00:13:15,294
              Oof!

258
00:13:16,196 --> 00:13:19,231
Is there anything in Yakyakistan
    that isn't the best?

259
00:13:19,733 --> 00:13:21,800
   Yes! Wait. No!

260
00:13:21,902 --> 00:13:22,701
    Yaks best.

261
00:13:23,003 --> 00:13:25,103
          No claws, no
           wings, no fire.

262
00:13:25,205 --> 00:13:27,238
       What is it exactly
        you're proud of?

263
00:13:27,340 --> 00:13:29,240
                  Whoa, cool it.

264
00:13:29,342 --> 00:13:32,911
      No need to harsh Yona's
      love for her heritage. OK?

265
00:13:33,013 --> 00:13:33,913
                            Aww.

266
00:13:34,014 --> 00:13:37,214
    Are we not being sweet and
  friendly enough for you, pony?

267
00:13:37,517 --> 00:13:38,650
That was sarcasm, right?

268
00:13:38,752 --> 00:13:41,352
Because you weren't
being sweet or nice?

269
00:13:41,454 --> 00:13:44,555
 Maybe dragons and griffons are
 just too tough for friendship.

270
00:13:45,759 --> 00:13:46,658
Yaks tough.

271
00:13:46,760 --> 00:13:48,360
Just not nasty.

272
00:13:48,562 --> 00:13:50,395
                 Who you calling
                  nasty, klutz?

273
00:13:51,799 --> 00:13:55,000
        OK, break it up!
         BREAK. IT. UP!

274
00:13:55,502 --> 00:13:57,269
What is going
on here?

275
00:13:57,671 --> 00:14:01,172
   Just a friendly discussion
  about the magic of friendship

276
00:14:01,274 --> 00:14:03,208
        amongst friends.

277
00:14:03,510 --> 00:14:06,077
          Everypony--I
        mean--everyONE--

278
00:14:06,179 --> 00:14:07,578
     go to your next class!

279
00:14:09,650 --> 00:14:10,749
                    I just can't
                     believe it.

280
00:14:10,951 --> 00:14:11,767
             Fights breaking out

281
00:14:11,868 --> 00:14:13,784
        when they're supposed to
         be learnin' friendship?

282
00:14:14,187 --> 00:14:16,755
Things definitely aren't
going as "by the book"

283
00:14:16,857 --> 00:14:18,256
as Twilight planned.

284
00:14:18,558 --> 00:14:21,426
      That's because we're
       terrible teachers!

285
00:14:21,628 --> 00:14:25,029
      Face it. This school
        isn't gonna work.

286
00:14:28,735 --> 00:14:30,168
       Applejack: Fights breaking out
        in the hallways!

287
00:14:31,905 --> 00:14:33,738
        I don't look like
           that! Do I?

288
00:14:35,275 --> 00:14:36,208
            I get it.

289
00:14:36,309 --> 00:14:38,842
   Things are getting off to a
  rougher start than expected.

290
00:14:39,145 --> 00:14:40,512
         But that's OK!

291
00:14:40,914 --> 00:14:43,348
  Who are you and what have you
   done with Twilight Sparkle?

292
00:14:44,518 --> 00:14:47,218
    Every school in Equestria
      follows these rules.

293
00:14:47,320 --> 00:14:49,554
        As long as we do
       too, we'll be fine.

294
00:14:49,956 --> 00:14:51,256
Maybe we should...

295
00:14:51,458 --> 00:14:52,491
try something new?

296
00:14:52,693 --> 00:14:54,492
         The EEA will be
       here this afternoon

297
00:14:54,594 --> 00:14:55,895
   for Friends and Family Day.

298
00:14:55,996 --> 00:14:58,797
 They need to see a school that
    follows their guidelines.

299
00:14:58,899 --> 00:15:02,100
    Even if those guidelines
       aren't working..?

300
00:15:02,602 --> 00:15:05,737
   Well, then, we have to try
  harder and make sure they do.

301
00:15:07,508 --> 00:15:10,909
    Another morning, another
 chance to inspire our students.

302
00:15:15,248 --> 00:15:18,550
           Hey! Professor Dash's
            class is this way.

303
00:15:19,352 --> 00:15:20,418
Where are you going?

304
00:15:20,520 --> 00:15:22,987
 You're not...
skipping, are you?

305
00:15:23,089 --> 00:15:24,889
         That's exactly
        what we're doing.

306
00:15:25,091 --> 00:15:26,324
But Friends and
 Family Day--

307
00:15:26,426 --> 00:15:28,660
               --is AFTER class.

308
00:15:29,062 --> 00:15:33,264
      Relax! This is just a
  quick... mental health break.

309
00:15:35,602 --> 00:15:36,601
That sounds legit.

310
00:15:36,803 --> 00:15:37,636
We're in.

311
00:15:37,738 --> 00:15:39,704
                  I guess I'll
                tag along too...

312
00:15:40,006 --> 00:15:42,907
       make sure you don't
        get into.. trouble.

313
00:15:46,413 --> 00:15:47,679
Fluttershy: This
way, Angel.

314
00:15:47,881 --> 00:15:49,180
           Professor Fluttershy!

315
00:15:49,282 --> 00:15:50,782
We're busted!

316
00:15:53,653 --> 00:15:56,087
Oh my! What are
you all doing?

317
00:15:56,289 --> 00:15:57,889
Aren't classes
that way?

318
00:15:59,226 --> 00:16:02,995
       A generosity field
        trip, dahhhling.

319
00:16:03,697 --> 00:16:05,830
     I'm taking the students
      to the laaake...

320
00:16:06,232 --> 00:16:08,533
         to look at our
       divine reflections.

321
00:16:10,637 --> 00:16:12,670
      Oh. That sounds nice.

322
00:16:12,772 --> 00:16:13,672
            Have fun!

323
00:16:19,646 --> 00:16:22,513
          I take back everything
           I said about you.

324
00:16:22,715 --> 00:16:24,082
                  That was cool!

325
00:16:24,284 --> 00:16:24,983
             Thanks!

326
00:16:25,285 --> 00:16:26,985
       Wait...What did you
          say about me?

327
00:16:29,055 --> 00:16:31,022
   You're sure sticking to the
     book is going to work?

328
00:16:31,324 --> 00:16:32,958
         My friends can
        handle anything.

329
00:16:33,060 --> 00:16:35,526
 They'll have these problems
turned around before we know it.

330
00:16:35,828 --> 00:16:36,794
                       Problems?

331
00:16:37,764 --> 00:16:38,997
      Chancellor Neighsay!

332
00:16:39,199 --> 00:16:40,065
          You're here!

333
00:16:40,567 --> 00:16:44,502
          Yes. And you
        seem unprepared.

334
00:16:44,704 --> 00:16:46,137
    If there are problems...

335
00:16:46,439 --> 00:16:48,506
          Problems? Ha!
         Of course not!

336
00:16:48,608 --> 00:16:50,208
        We can't wait to
        show you around.

337
00:16:52,579 --> 00:16:53,478
         [nervous laugh]

338
00:16:54,580 --> 00:16:59,050
     And that's why griffons
  breathe fire when we get mad.

339
00:16:59,252 --> 00:17:00,551
          They do NOT!

340
00:17:00,653 --> 00:17:01,986
         Wait, do they?

341
00:17:02,088 --> 00:17:03,421
           No. Really?

342
00:17:03,523 --> 00:17:05,590
Griffons just full of hot air.

343
00:17:08,061 --> 00:17:10,194
And yaks are actually
good at jokes.

344
00:17:10,296 --> 00:17:11,062
How about that?

345
00:17:11,264 --> 00:17:12,998
                What are dragons
                  good at?

346
00:17:13,600 --> 00:17:14,833
          Competition.

347
00:17:14,935 --> 00:17:16,167
      Who's up for a race?

348
00:17:19,773 --> 00:17:21,073
          Rainbow Dash!

349
00:17:21,274 --> 00:17:22,674
        Why aren't you in
        class teaching?

350
00:17:22,876 --> 00:17:24,475
         Because my
       students are gone!

351
00:17:25,545 --> 00:17:27,646
   Uh, gone...somewhere else!

352
00:17:28,048 --> 00:17:29,481
     Doing a loyalty lesson.

353
00:17:29,583 --> 00:17:32,984
And I was just going to
grab, uh ... this pencil!

354
00:17:33,086 --> 00:17:34,118
Because they need it.

355
00:17:34,220 --> 00:17:35,086
Wherever they are.

356
00:17:35,188 --> 00:17:35,788
Which I know...

357
00:17:35,889 --> 00:17:38,089
     cause.. I'm the teacher.

358
00:17:38,491 --> 00:17:41,960
    I see. Well, Chancellor,
     we have other classes.

359
00:17:42,062 --> 00:17:44,962
         We can just...---
            Let's follow the... professor.

360
00:17:45,365 --> 00:17:48,933
        I'm quite curious about
       this "lesson in loyalty."

361
00:17:53,473 --> 00:17:55,473
      <i> Twilight: Of course,</i>
       <i> we want to instill</i>

362
00:17:55,575 --> 00:17:57,776
       <i> a sense of loyalty</i>
        <i> towards others.</i>

363
00:17:58,378 --> 00:18:01,079
      <i> We encourage acts of</i>
    <i> generosity and kindness.</i>

364
00:18:04,184 --> 00:18:06,751
   Figured we shouldn't be the
  only ones enjoying the view.

365
00:18:07,153 --> 00:18:12,390
  AGH! YAKS NOT BEST AT FLYING!

366
00:18:12,492 --> 00:18:15,059
      <i> An appreciation for</i>
     <i> the value of laughter.</i>

367
00:18:15,261 --> 00:18:17,628
         FLYING IS BEST!

368
00:18:17,730 --> 00:18:19,931
Congratulations, Yona!

369
00:18:20,033 --> 00:18:23,334
You are officially the weirdest
thing I've seen so far!

370
00:18:23,536 --> 00:18:25,069
       What do you say, Ocellus?

371
00:18:25,171 --> 00:18:28,005
              Can you be weirder
              than a flying yak?

372
00:18:30,377 --> 00:18:31,910
               OH!

373
00:18:32,012 --> 00:18:34,645
      ... and to always be
    honest in any situation.

374
00:18:34,747 --> 00:18:36,314
     Honesty is imperative.

375
00:18:36,516 --> 00:18:38,683
        Princess, are we
        going in circles?

376
00:18:38,985 --> 00:18:40,285
     Uh...look at the time!

377
00:18:40,487 --> 00:18:42,754
  We'd better head to the lake
   for Friends and Family Day!

378
00:18:42,856 --> 00:18:45,356
  I'm sure all the students and
    faculty will be there!

379
00:18:56,669 --> 00:18:57,502
             Ha ha!

380
00:18:59,239 --> 00:19:00,505
                What is that!?

381
00:19:09,616 --> 00:19:11,416
   THE SCHOOL IS UNDER ATTACK!

382
00:19:19,592 --> 00:19:20,725
         Oh my goodness!

383
00:19:20,927 --> 00:19:22,328
              Whoa!

384
00:19:32,005 --> 00:19:35,340
    Uh, maybe skipping class
      wasn't the best idea?

385
00:19:36,042 --> 00:19:37,809
          How DARE you!

386
00:19:38,011 --> 00:19:39,844
     This act of aggression
        against ponies--

387
00:19:39,946 --> 00:19:41,412
                   I'm so sorry,
                    Chancellor.

388
00:19:41,614 --> 00:19:44,082
  We clearly had some students
   get a little carried away.

389
00:19:44,284 --> 00:19:45,884
             THOSE are students?

390
00:19:46,186 --> 00:19:48,319
But, you said you were
opening this school

391
00:19:48,421 --> 00:19:49,854
      to protect Equestria!

392
00:19:50,056 --> 00:19:53,258
To defend ponies from
dangerous creatures

393
00:19:53,560 --> 00:19:56,261
who don't have our best
interests at heart.

394
00:19:56,463 --> 00:19:58,863
    My school teaches for all
     of us to work together

395
00:19:58,965 --> 00:19:59,832
       through friendship.

396
00:20:01,034 --> 00:20:03,668
       And how do you know
        these.. creatures

397
00:20:03,770 --> 00:20:07,105
 won't take what they've learned
   here and use it against us?

398
00:20:07,507 --> 00:20:09,207
Friendship isn't
just for ponies.

399
00:20:09,309 --> 00:20:10,675
                   It should be!

400
00:20:11,277 --> 00:20:13,678
       Unicorn think yaks
       no need friendship?

401
00:20:14,280 --> 00:20:17,248
                 Maybe yaks no
               need pony school!

402
00:20:17,450 --> 00:20:22,386
Well, then perhaps you
should return to your kind.

403
00:20:22,588 --> 00:20:24,322
    "Your kind!?"

404
00:20:24,424 --> 00:20:26,290
      Smolder? Let's go!

405
00:20:29,229 --> 00:20:31,796
      Queen Novo will want
        to hear of this.

406
00:20:33,233 --> 00:20:35,700
        This place seemed
          lame anyways.

407
00:20:39,572 --> 00:20:40,306
           It's fine.

408
00:20:40,607 --> 00:20:43,341
      We know not everypony
     sees us the way you do.

409
00:20:43,643 --> 00:20:44,943
        We're used to it.

410
00:20:48,281 --> 00:20:51,215
Princess Celestia helped me
reach out to all the kingdoms.

411
00:20:51,317 --> 00:20:53,001
When she hears you closed
the school because--

412
00:20:53,102 --> 00:20:56,586
         Because you failed to
       meet the EEA's standards?

413
00:20:56,889 --> 00:20:57,755
What!?

414
00:20:57,857 --> 00:20:59,423
         Irresponsible teachers.

415
00:20:59,525 --> 00:21:01,059
        Students skipping class!

416
00:21:01,161 --> 00:21:02,994
             Endangering ponies!

417
00:21:03,096 --> 00:21:05,130
      Your school is a disaster.

418
00:21:05,732 --> 00:21:09,133
    Perhaps if you had higher
 standards for who was admitted,

419
00:21:09,235 --> 00:21:10,868
  this could have been avoided.

420
00:21:11,804 --> 00:21:12,804
          Regardless...

421
00:21:22,915 --> 00:21:24,849
      By order of the EEA,

422
00:21:24,951 --> 00:21:28,686
          I am shutting
        this school DOWN.

423
00:21:28,888 --> 00:21:29,721
               Oh!

